{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 00:58:23.764092", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nScope and Topology\\n- Multi-tier Clos (fat-tree) using eBGP with FRR.\\n- Devices in this pod: super_spine_router_0 (AS65000), spine_router_0_0 (AS65100), spine_router_0_1 (AS65101), leaf_router_0_0 (AS65200), leaf_router_0_1 (AS65201), hosts pc_0_0 (10.0.0.2/24), pc_0_1 (10.0.1.2/24).\\n\\n1) Data-plane Health (Reachability)\\n- Host-to-host connectivity is normal:\\n  - pc_0_0 -> pc_0_1: 0% loss, RTT avg ~2.53 ms.\\n  - pc_0_1 -> pc_0_0: 0% loss, RTT avg ~2.08 ms.\\n- Broad reachability sampling across many hosts/subnets shows 0% packet loss and low RTTs (generally 1–5 ms), indicating fabric-wide reachability is intact.\\n\\n2) Control-plane Health (BGP/FRR)\\n- FRR service status: active (running) on all routers (leaves, spines, super-spine).\\n- BGP sessions:\\n  - leaf_router_0_0 (AS65200): 8 eBGP neighbors, all Established; PfxRcd ~31 per neighbor.\\n  - leaf_router_0_1 (AS65201): 8 eBGP neighbors, all Established; PfxRcd ~31 per neighbor.\\n  - spine_router_0_0 (AS65100): 12 neighbors (4 super-spine + 8 leaves), all Established.\\n    - Super-spine neighbors show PfxRcd 24 each.\\n    - Leaf neighbors (AS65200–65203) show PfxRcd 4; (AS65204–65207) show PfxRcd 1.\\n  - spine_router_0_1 (AS65101): 12 neighbors (4 super-spine + 8 leaves), all Established.\\n    - Super-spine neighbors show PfxRcd 32 each.\\n    - Leaf neighbors show PfxRcd 32 each.\\n  - super_spine_router_0 (AS65000): 32 spine peers, all Established; PfxRcd 8 each.\\n- Routing tables:\\n  - Leaves originate their local /24 (10.0.0.0/24 on leaf 0_0; 10.0.1.0/24 on leaf 0_1) and learn all other 10.x.y.0/24 prefixes via spines.\\n  - Spines have wide route coverage for all 10.x.y.0/24 networks. spine_router_0_0 shows ECMP (4-way) via super-spine for many remote subnets; spine_router_0_1 similarly has full coverage via super-spine and leaf peers.\\n  - No missing critical routes for the tested subnets; BGP-learned routes are installed in FIB (B>* entries).\\n\\n3) Anomaly Detection and Localization\\n- No data-plane outage detected: end-to-end reachability is normal, no packet loss observed, and RTTs are consistent with expectations for a small lab fabric.\\n- Control-plane inconsistencies observed:\\n  - Uneven prefix counts from neighbors:\\n    - spine_router_0_0 receives fewer prefixes (24) from each super-spine neighbor, whereas spine_router_0_1 receives 32 from each super-spine neighbor.\\n    - spine_router_0_0 sees only 1 or 4 PfxRcd from certain leaf neighbors, while spine_router_0_1 sees 32 from each leaf neighbor.\\n  - These differences indicate asymmetric route propagation or policy filtering between super_spine_router_0 and spine_router_0_0 (or differing import/export policies on spine_router_0_0 vs spine_router_0_1).\\n  - Despite these differences, route coverage in the FIB on both spines appears complete for the tested subnets (data-plane unaffected).\\n- CLI discrepancy:\\n  - On spine_router_0_1, “show bgp ipv4 unicast 10.0.0.0/24” returned “Network not in table,” while the route table shows B>* 10.0.0.0/24 present via super-spine peers. This is likely a transient or command lookup quirk; not corroborated as a persistent control-plane fault.\\n\\n4) Root Cause Assessment (for identified abnormalities)\\n- The asymmetric BGP prefix counts likely stem from differences in BGP advertisement/acceptance policies or route propagation behavior on:\\n  - super_spine_router_0 toward spine_router_0_0, and/or\\n  - spine_router_0_0’s import filtering compared to spine_router_0_1.\\n- Leaves appear to (re)advertise more than only their local /24 to spines (e.g., PfxRcd 32 on spine_router_0_1 from a single leaf peer). This behavior is permitted by “no bgp ebgp-requires-policy” and suggests no export filtering, which is atypical in some Clos designs that restrict leaf advertisements. It explains high PfxRcd counts but is not currently causing reachability issues.\\n\\nSummary\\n- Network health: Data-plane is healthy with full reachability across tested prefixes and no loss.\\n- Abnormalities: Inconsistent BGP prefix counts between super-spine/spines and leaves/spines, suggesting non-uniform route propagation or policies. No immediate data-plane impact observed.\\n- Fault localization: If action were needed, investigation would focus on BGP policy/advertisement differences on super_spine_router_0 and spine_router_0_0 (compared to spine_router_0_1)., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='fba85fb2-563d-4e01-a543-abb8666b5bbc'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
